NBA ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
NUGGETS ON FIRST WINNING STREAK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Orlando Woolridge scored 32 points and Michael Adams 29 as the Denver Nuggets 
won two in a row for the first time this season, beating the Sacramento Kings, 
136-128, Thursday night at Denver. 
</P>
<P>
It was only Denver's third victory in 14 games. 
</P>
<P>
Sacramento suffered its 12th loss in 13 games. 
</P>
<P>
Wayman Tisdale scored 33 points for the Kings, who also got 22 from Lionel 
Simmons and Travis Mays and 20 from Antoine Carr. 
</P>
<P>
Portland 107, Minnesota 92 -- Clyde Drexler scored 21 points and Terry Porter 
added 20 as the Trail Blazers built a 20-point halftime lead and coasted at 
home to improve their record to 12-1. 
</P>
<P>
