<HEADLINE>
<P>
PARADE ESTIMATES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I see once again that you need to be reminded of the silliness of accepting 
parade crowd estimates at face value. 
</P>
<P>
I refer to the statement on the front of the Metro section (Nov. 26) concerning 
the Hollywood Christmas Parade. 
</P>
<P>
Arithmetic reveals that "about 750,000 spectators along the 3.2-mile route" 
would require packing people together 29% more densely than the mythical 1 
million who have been said to linethe 5.5-mile Rose Parade route. The actual 
number at the Rose Parades is really under 400,000 by more thoughtful 
estimates, so your Hollywood Parade estimate is even more grossly exaggerated. 
</P>
<P>
CHRISTOPHER LEE 
</P>
<P>
Pasadena 
</P>
