<TEXT>
<P>
San Diego police are searching for other victims of an extortion ring operating 
in East San Diego after the arrest of three suspects. 
</P>
<P>
Three men were arrested Wednesday on suspicion of extorting money from a number 
of businesses operated by Southeast Asians, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The suspects allegedly demanded money in exchange for protection and threatened 
to harm the victims or their families if they did not comply. 
</P>
<P>
