<P>
HERMOSA BEACH IS SITE FOR VOLLEYBALL CLINIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hermosa Beach joins the Assn. of Volleyball Professionals in sponsoring a 
clinic Saturday and Sunday at the Pier Avenue sand courts. It is open to youth 
age 9 to 14 and runs from 8 a.m. to noon. The cost is $20. Information: (213) 
318-0280. 
</P>
<P>
The cities of Manhattan Beach and Redondo Beach are offering a combined men's 
indoor volleyball league. Two leagues of six teams each are planned. 
Three-quarters of the members of each team must reside in either city. The cost 
is $100, plus $1 for each non-resident. A $50 forfeit fee is also required. 
Deadline to enroll is Dec. 7. Information: (213) 545-5621, Ext. 321. 
</P>
<P>
Pop's All-Pro Baseball Camp is back for a pair of winter sessions at the Lunada 
Bay Little League. The dates are Dec. 17-21 and Dec. 26-30. The camps feature 
scheduled appearances by professional baseball players. They run from 9 a.m. to 
3:30 p.m. The cost is $175 per session. Morning and afternoon extended 
child-care hours are available at no cost. Information: (213) 373-3805. 
</P>
<P>
The second South Bay Baseball Camp will be held Dec. 27-30 at Mira Costa High. 
The camp runs from 9 a.m. to 3 p.m. and is open to youths age 7 to 17. John 
Orton, a catcher with the Angels, is scheduled to take part in the instruction. 
The cost is $190. Information: (213) 318-1577. 
</P>
<P>
Inglewood is forming adult basketball leagues and tournaments to be played at 
Rogers Park. Tournament play begins Dec. 10 and costs $40, plus the cost of 
referees. League play begins Jan. 7 and costs $100 per team, plus referee fees. 
Information: (213) 412-5370. 
</P>
<P>
Cal State Dominguez Hills soccer Coach Marine Cano will sponsor two sessions of 
his annual soccer camp. Session I will be Dec. 26-28. The cost is $65. Session 
II runs Dec. 29-30. The cost is $50. A special rate for all five days is $85. 
Instruction is for boys and girls age 5 to 13 and runs from 9 a.m. to 1 p.m. 
each day. A T-shirt is included. The camps will take place on the university's 
lower soccer field next to the tennis courts. Players must bring a ball. 
Information: (213) 782-8324. 
</P>
<P>
The Los Angeles Heat will sponsor soccer skills camps at La Marina School in 
Manhattan Beach and Columbia Park in Torrance on Jan. 2-5. Sessions, designed 
for boys and girls age 5 and 6, will be held from 9 a.m. to 4 p.m. each day. 
The cost is $100 per player. Groups of six or more players receive a $20 per 
player discount. Balls, T-shirts, two tickets to a Heat game and other items 
will be presented to each participant. Information: (213) 318-3995. 
</P>
</TEXT>
