BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bush Signs Tuna Labeling Law: Both tuna industry leaders and such one-time 
antagonists as the Dolphin Coalition, a Washington-based umbrella group of 37 
conservation organizations, applauded the signing by President Bush of laws 
setting standards for "dolphin-safe" tuna. Packaged as amendments to the 
Magnuson Fishery Conservation and Management Act of 1976, the new statutes 
define what canners must do before labeling their product as dolphin safe. Many 
in the canning industry favored the bill because it provides a uniform 
standard. 
</P>
</TEXT>
