<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRADLEY HONORED AS ALL-AMERICAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Freddie Bradley of Moorpark College has been named a first-team junior college 
All-American by J.C. Grid-Wire. 
</P>
<P>
Bradley (6 feet, 195 pounds), a second-team selection last season, scored 180 
points, rushed for 1,946 yards and had 2,428 all-purpose yards in leading 
Moorpark to an 8-2 record and a berth in the Western State Conference Bowl. 
</P>
<P>
Sophomore Lolesio Takapu (6-2, 235) of WSC Southern Division champion Glendale 
was selected as a second-team linebacker. 
</P>
<P>
Honorable-mention selections included Santa Monica quarterback Jeff Barrett, a 
former standout at Burroughs High, Glendale running back Bobby Webster, 
Moorpark defensive lineman Ron Nielsen, Valley defensive back Sam Edwards, 
Valley punter Edward Bunn and Ventura all-purpose runner Chris Thomas. 
</P>
