<P>
Wells Fargo Acquisition Approved: Wells Fargo &amp; Co. received Office of 
Thrift Supervision approval to buy Great American Bank's 130 California 
branches for $491 million. 
</P>
<P>
The regulators' approval was the last obstacle facing the deal first announced 
last July. The first phase of the sale, including branches in San Diego, Orange 
and Riverside counties, will close today, Wells Fargo said. Wells Fargo said it 
plans no layoffs among the 1,900 Great American employees it is absorbing, even 
though the San Francisco-based bank plans to close seven of the 64 Great 
American branches it is acquiring in San Diego County. The OTS also approved 
Great American's capital plan, giving it until 1994 to raise its capital levels 
to minimum regulatory requirements. 
