<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: YORBA LINDA; 
</P>
<P>
PREGNANT WOMAN BOUND AND ROBBED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 23-year-old woman in her ninth month of pregnancy was bound, blindfolded and 
robbed by three men, one of whom posed as a deliveryman, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The robbery occurred in the 4200 block of Avocado Avenue at 9:11 a.m. Thursday 
when a man dressed as a deliveryman and driving a white, red and blue mail-type 
truck knocked on the victim's door, police said. 
</P>
<P>
When the unidentified victim opened the door, the man pointed a gun at her and 
walked inside, police said. The gunman was joined by two other men who helped 
blindfold and tie the victim, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The robbers ransacked the victim's house for about 15 minutes taking an unknown 
amount of property, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Before the robbers left they untied the victim and told her to wait before 
calling authorities, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Several minutes later the victim called police and was taken to Placentia Linda 
Hospital, in Placentia with a bruised wrist, police said. She was treated at 
the hospital and released without injury to her unborn child. 
</P>
</TEXT>
