<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
MISSOURI KANSAS CITY GETS HOT IN SECOND HALF TO ROLL PAST SCC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Missouri Kansas City rallied in the second half for an 88-69 victory over 
Southern California College in a nonconference men's basketball game Thursday 
at Kansas City. 
</P>
<P>
Southern California (3-2) led at the half, 35-34, but Missouri Kansas City shot 
62% in the second half to pull away. 
</P>
<P>
Ronnie Schmitz scored 18 points for Missouri Kansas City (3-2). 
</P>
<P>
Kent Denmon scored 15 points and Anthony Davis added 12 points and a game-high 
14 rebounds for Missouri Kansas City. Terry Dickerson and David Robinson added 
10 points each for the Kangaroos, who have a nine-game home winning streak. 
</P>
<P>
Jeff Bickmore scored 23 and Mike Henjum added 16 for SCC. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
In the Azusa Pacific tournament: 
</P>
<P>
Colorado Christian 97, Pacific Christian 76 -- Phil Garcia scored 21 points for 
Pacific Christian, which lost in the first round. 
</P>
<P>
Kenny Crawford added 20 and Kenny Kao 11 for Pacific Christian. 
