PRACTICAL VIEW; 
</P>
<P>
TURNING A MINUS INTO A PLUS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CINDY LaFAVRE YORKS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Have you bought a jacket for $200 one week only to see it marked down to $150 
the next? 
</P>
<P>
A survey of local stores reveals that you can collect the difference. 
</P>
<P>
* Saks Fifth Avenue: refund of the difference between sale and regular price 
can be collected within three weeks of purchase. 
</P>
<P>
* The Broadway: customers with receipts can collect the difference if the 
garment goes on sale within 10 days of the date of purchase. Neiman Marcus and 
I. Magnin have the same policy. 
</P>
<P>
* Robinson's: refunds difference within one week of purchase. 
</P>
<P>
* May Co. and The Limited refund a difference at any time. CINDY LaFAVRE YORKS 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, THIS: $200 jacket purchased one week. ; Photo, MINUS THIS: On sale for 
$150 the next week, equals: A $50 refund to buyer. 
</P>
