<P>
NUN WINS SPORTS CAR IN RAFFLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
YAKIMA, Wash. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Roman Catholic nun won a $13,000, fire-engine-red sports car in a raffle to 
benefit her school. 
</P>
<P>
Sister Rebecca Berghoff, 65, said she was aghast when she was declared the 
winner in the raffle for the St. Joseph-Marquette School, where she is 
principal. 
</P>
<P>
She said she bought 30 $1 tickets for Saturday's drawing. About 32,000 tickets 
were sold for the school, which has 300 pupils in kindergarten through eighth 
grade. 
</P>
<P>
She returned the Geo Storm to the dealer and said the refund will help ease the 
school's budget problems. 
</P>
<P>
Besides, she said, it wasn't appropriate "for a nun to be streaking around in a 
car like that." 
</P>
</TEXT>
