<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
8 NBA PLAYERS FINED FOR FIGHTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The NBA fined eight players from the Atlanta Hawks and Detroit Pistons a total 
of $6,750 today for their roles in an altercation during a game last week. 
</P>
<P>
Bill Laimbeer of the Pistons was fined $2,000 for initiating the incident by 
bumping Dominique Wilkins to the floor with his hip and pushing him twice in 
last Tuesday night's game. 
</P>
<P>
Wilkins was fined $1,000 for charging Laimbeer. Kevin Willis of the Hawks was 
fined $1,000, Vinnie Johnson of the Pistons was fined $750 and Doc Rivers of 
the Hawks was fined $500, each for taking part in the altercation. 
</P>
<P>
Three other Pistons -- William Bedford, James Edwards and John Salley -- were 
fined $500 each for leaving the bench area during the incident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
