<HEADLINE>
<P>
SHORT TAKES; 
</P>
<P>
HAYES, WEAVER TO SHARE AWARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Actors Helen Hayes and Dennis Weaver will share the annual Louella O. Parsons 
Award bestowed annually by the Hollywood Women's Press Club for recognition of 
their humanitarian efforts. 
</P>
<P>
The presentations will be a highlight of the 50th anniversary Golden Apple 
Awards luncheon Dec. 9 at the Beverly Hilton. 
</P>
<P>
The 1990 award will be the first dual presentation. 
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the club announced that Bob Hope will be the recipient of the first 
All-Time Man of the Year Award. 
</P>
<P>
The Hollywood Women's Press Club was founded in 1928 by Parsons and 10 other 
Hollywood columnists. 
</P>
</TEXT>
