<P>
BLACK &amp; DECKER CUT, SUES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BALTIMORE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A scene in "Die Hard 2" in which Bruce Willis takes a power drill to an airport 
air duct ended up on the cutting-room floor, and now 20th Century Fox could end 
up in court. 
</P>
<P>
Black &amp; Decker Inc. has filed suit in federal court in Baltimore, accusing 
the filmmaker and the marketing firm Krown-Young &amp; Rubicam of failing to 
fulfill a promise that one of its drills would be featured in the film. 
</P>
<P>
Black &amp; Decker said in court papers filed Nov. 7 that it had planned an ad 
campaign based on the scene. 
</P>
<P>
The company is seeking at least $150,000. It accused Fox, the film's 
distributor, and Krown-Young &amp; Rubicam of negligence and breach of 
contract. 
</P>
</TEXT>
